This paper discusses link recommendation methods for social networks, which involves analyzing social interactions and relationships between users. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper also discusses learning-based and proximity-based methods, which fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR), respectively. The paper also mentions economic theories, which could potentially fall under the category of databases (cs.DB). Finally, the paper proposes future research directions, which could fall under the category of social computing (cs.SOC).
